            <arrangement id="aspace_5e3b9fd731c8580ea507305ede9b9357">
               <head>Arrangement</head>
               <p>The series is arranged alphabetically by author. Each author's writings are arranged alphabetically by title. A group of three poems by George Dillon, Kathleen Foster Campbell and Gladys Campbell are filed together at the end of the series.</p>
            </arrangement>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_f2ca4139f2ddddeae18c3503f02571c8">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Series II, Writings of Others, is chiefly comprised of poems by Gladys Campbell and Janet Lewis. It also contains poems by George Dillon and Kathleen Foster Campbell, a bibliography of Lewis's writings and an essay by David Levin on Kathleen Foster Campbell's <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                     <part>Then and Now</part>
                  </title>.</p>
               <p>Writings by Janet Lewis include poems set to music by Vernon Haskins and Alva Henderson. The series also includes two of Gladys Campbell's poems that were set to music by Wilbur Lesemann, the brother of Maurice Lesemann, and Vernon Haskins.</p>
            </scopecontent>
